5. THE TORVALDS PROVISO
"If you think your users are idiots, only idiots will use it." 
This software assumes the user is competent. Any modification that 
intentionally degrades performance or adds bloat to the core logic 
is a violation of the "Pure Power" principle.

6. NO WARRANTY
This software is provided "AS IS", without warranty of any kind. 
The author (hypernova-developer) is not responsible for any system 
failures or excessive speed achieved by this software.

7. THE ANTI-EXPLOIT & ANTI-MINING CLAUSE
This software is a guest on the CPU. It shall not be used to mine 
cryptocurrency, execute unauthorized telemetry, or perform any
background tasks that degrade hardware longevity for third-party
gain. Any attempt to turn 'Pure Power' into 'Parasitic Power' is 
a breach of this license.

8. HARDWARE-CENTRIC OPTIMIZATION MANDATE
Any fork or derivative of this software must prioritize direct hardware
communication (Bare Metal philosophy). Introducing abstraction layers that
increase latency or memory footprint unnecessarily is considered a violation
of the developer's intent. Efficiency is not an option; it is a requirement.
(Python-like VM based languages are still supported.)

9. THE NON-SUBSCRIPTION EDICT
This software, and all its derivatives, shall remain free from subscription-based
paywalls. Access to the full power of the machine is a fundamental right of the
user. No 'Activation Watermarks' or 'Premium Locked Features' shall ever be implemented.

